Dialogue: 0,0:00:01.19,0:00:07.35,Default,,0,0,0,,The most crucial moment in life is during decision making.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:09.15,0:00:13.80,Default,,0,0,0,,The Pacific War taught us the preciousness of peace.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:14.26,0:00:19.42,Default,,0,0,0,,But also instilled \Nnumerous lessons on how to live.{unsure, lit is "for the sake of living, precepts, numerous left behind"}
Dialogue: 0,0:00:24.38,0:00:31.39,Sign,,0,0,0,,{\fade(100,700)\c&H0007DF&\fs100\b1\bord0\blur1}Animentary\N{\b\c&HE0DBF3&}Decision
Dialogue: 0,0:00:35.41,0:00:43.33,Default,,0,0,0,,Wit is your weapon{honestly no clue what is megurase here, deepl says "rack one's brain"}\NRemember to use your head{智恵をめぐらせ 頭を使え}
Dialogue: 0,0:00:43.33,0:00:50.95,Default,,0,0,0,,Repress your anguish, \NIf you are a man{悩み抜け抜け 男なら}
Dialogue: 0,0:00:50.95,0:00:58.86,Default,,0,0,0,,One decision is enough \NTo make others cry or laugh{泣くも笑うも 決断ひとつ}
Dialogue: 0,0:00:58.86,0:01:06.69,Default,,0,0,0,,If you win, don't hold your head high, \NIf you lose, don't cry{勝っておごるな 敗れて泣くな}
Dialogue: 0,0:01:06.69,0:01:14.57,Default,,0,0,0,,Men, don't you ever let other see your tears{男 涙は見せぬもの}
Comment: 0,0:01:34.91,0:01:34.95,Default,,0,0,0,,{ch}
Comment: 0,0:24:43.11,0:24:43.15,Default,,0,0,0,,{ch}
Dialogue: 0,0:24:43.15,0:24:47.56,Default,,0,0,0,,If you're a man, let's put your strength to test{男だったら　力を試せ}
Dialogue: 0,0:24:47.56,0:24:51.90,Default,,0,0,0,,If you are a man, keep your hopes sizzling{男だったら　希望(のぞみ)を燃やせ}
Dialogue: 0,0:24:51.90,0:24:56.26,Default,,0,0,0,,If you are a man, don't lose your heart{男だったら　くじけるな}
Dialogue: 0,0:24:56.26,0:25:04.83,Default,,0,0,0,,Because there's just you and me, a man and a man{俺もおまえも　男と男}
Dialogue: 0,0:25:04.83,0:25:13.06,Default,,0,0,0,,With crimson blood flowing in our veins all the same{おなじ真赤な　血が通う}
Dialogue: 0,0:25:07.78,0:25:12.30,Sign,,0,0,0,,{\pos(720,700)}Brought to you by the Sorcery Party \Nѫ~ѫ\N"Lux in Tenebris"
Dialogue: 0,0:25:12.30,0:25:18.06,Sign,,0,0,0,,{\fs47\bord2\fade(0,600)\an6\pos(730,520)}Translation by \NQuality Checking by \NSupplementary materials by \NVideo by
Dialogue: 0,0:25:12.30,0:25:18.06,Sign,,0,0,0,,{\fs47\bord2\fade(0,600)\an4\pos(760,520)}Perevodildo\N Ziusudra\N History Asian \N Moozzi2
Dialogue: 0,0:01:39.95,0:01:45.68,Default,,0,0,0,,Ever since the surprise attack on Pearl Harbor, \Nthe Combined Fleet under Isoroku Yamamoto
Dialogue: 0,0:01:45.68,0:01:51.34,Default,,0,0,0,,has seen consecutive victories in all its operations \Non Solomon Islands and the Indian Ocean.{/kept winning a streak of tactical victories}
Dialogue: 0,0:01:52.98,0:01:55.49,Default,,0,0,0,,Since April 1942,
Dialogue: 0,0:01:55.49,0:01:59.57,Default,,0,0,0,,the Combined Fleet Command, \Nactively backed by Commander-in-Chief Yamamoto,
Dialogue: 0,0:01:59.57,0:02:05.02,Default,,0,0,0,,planned the Midway invasion operation.{lit is just "proposed midway operation/maneuvres" but methinks this is implied; besides, invasion and occupation is what was actually planned irl} \NThe Naval General Staff had been pressured to approve it.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:06.12,0:02:10.98,Default,,0,0,0,,Midway invasion operation \Nwas aimed at capturing Midway to use it as an air base,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:10.98,0:02:15.36,Default,,0,0,0,,at the same time, \Ncurtailing American naval operations in the area.{lit: blocking maneuver operations from american side from this direction}
Dialogue: 0,0:02:15.36,0:02:20.69,Default,,0,0,0,,Moreover, the underlying plan was to decoy \Nthe main American fleet and crush it in an open battle. {/besides, the strategy has been ...}
Dialogue: 0,0:02:19.76,0:02:26.92,Sign,,0,0,200,,{\fade(300,0)\c&HFBF2F7&\1a&H00&\b1\blur1\bord0}{ミッドウェイ海戦(前編)}Episode 2 \N{\fs100}Battle of Midway (Part 1){/initial/first half}
Dialogue: 0,0:02:27.58,0:02:32.65,Default,,0,0,0,,However, the Naval General Staff understated \Nthe strategic unimportance of Midway Island.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:32.65,0:02:37.98,Default,,0,0,0,,The Combined Fleet Command were in heated confrontation with them, \Nuntil the Commander-in-Chief...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:37.98,0:02:41.53,Default,,0,0,0,,If this operation is not approved, \NI resign as Commander-in-Chief.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:41.53,0:02:44.55,Default,,0,0,0,,Just as before the surprise attack at Pearl Harbor,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:44.55,0:02:49.27,Default,,0,0,0,,In one jostle, Commander-in-Chief Yamamoto \Nwas able to push the initiative through.{/voice of authority overcame the opposition}
Dialogue: 0,0:02:51.61,0:02:54.75,Default,,0,0,0,,He believed \Nthat the homeland's protection, {/secure the japan's safety}{trivia: the attack on midway was provoked by doolittle's raid - the bombing of tokyo, conducted from american carrier}
Dialogue: 0,0:02:54.75,0:02:58.66,Default,,0,0,0,,came with the need to seal the fate \Nof the American fleet on the Pacific. {actually just "task force/mobile unit"}
Dialogue: 0,0:03:00.84,0:03:06.29,Default,,0,0,0,,That day, the Japanese Navy\Nwas celebrating the 37th Navy Day. {no clue what is "kyuu" in the beginning, wisper has it "第九"}{https://ja.wikipedia.org/wiki/%E6%B5%B7%E8%BB%8D%E8%A8%98%E5%BF%B5%E6%97%A5}
Dialogue: 0,0:03:06.29,0:03:10.46,Default,,0,0,0,,Year is 1942. May 27th.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:11.23,0:03:13.27,Default,,0,0,0,,Led by Vice Admiral Chuichi Nagumo,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:13.27,0:03:21.17,Default,,0,0,0,,Akagi, Kaga, Hiryu, Soryu - four aircraft carriers, \Ncomprising the core of the first Mobile Fleet {used this name in the ep1}{/the 1st ... centered around ...}
Dialogue: 0,0:03:21.17,0:03:25.52,Default,,0,0,0,,under the veil of morning mist, \Nhad set sail from the Island of Hashira in Hiroshima Bay.{shutsugeki is actually "sortie; sally; attack" but they are using it very liberally}{/Hashirajima}
Dialogue: 0,0:03:57.67,0:04:03.24,Default,,0,0,0,,Commanding the main forces{主力部隊 - important trivia: here this implies a surface fleet that's going to lie in ambush during the operation at a distance from Nagumo's task force} from his new flagship{idk what's kikan, would trust HA here} Yamato, \NCommander-in-Chief Yamamoto {he also adds for the first time but "new" already implies that}
Dialogue: 0,0:04:03.24,0:04:09.10,Default,,0,0,0,,would follow them two days later, on the 29th, \Ndeparting for a voyage of 480km. {lit: she will become a shutsugeki; english wiki is wrong about that, but she indeed set sail on 29th}
Dialogue: 0,0:04:19.92,0:04:23.37,Default,,0,0,0,,The Invasion of Midway took place \Nconcurrently to the Aleutian Islands.{/at the same time as seizure/capture of ...}{I have sources that say invasion of aleutians was a feint/diversion from actual attack on midway, and I have sources that say they just happened to coincide, no actual forward-thinking behind it; either way, I don't think it matters all that much}
Dialogue: 0,0:04:23.37,0:04:27.25,Default,,0,0,0,,Which was then the biggest operation \Nin the history of Japanese Navy.{not sure what is guuzen here, trust HA; coincidence; chance; accident; fortuity​ - I think guuzen here means that the most amount of ships are operating simultaneously/coincide}
Dialogue: 0,0:04:27.80,0:04:34.69,Default,,0,0,0,,The total force is 350 ships, \N1000 aircraft, personnel - around 100,000.{/soldiers/manpower}
Dialogue: 0,0:04:35.42,0:04:37.84,Default,,0,0,0,,The combined fleet is dispatched in full. {most likely 総出動の艦が but I don't get it - "general/overall marching of warships", maybe "in full/with all ships"}
Dialogue: 0,0:04:43.89,0:04:44.86,Default,,0,0,0,, Banzai!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:44.86,0:04:46.07,Default,,0,0,0,,Our heroes!{guess}
Dialogue: 0,0:04:47.82,0:04:50.31,Default,,0,0,0,,The Japanese fleet is invincible!{HA has it "The Japanese Navy is in full force." and I'm too lazy to get to the bottom of this}
Dialogue: 0,0:05:00.20,0:05:02.81,Default,,0,0,0,,Radios have been playing \Narmy marches since morning! {/nothing but ...}{technically, "warship marches"}
Dialogue: 0,0:05:02.81,0:05:04.13,Default,,0,0,0,,Everyone's rooting for us! {lit: a gift/present to us}
Dialogue: 0,0:05:04.13,0:05:05.69,Default,,0,0,0,,Must be so, indeed!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:05.69,0:05:07.68,Default,,0,0,0,,It seems, our victory is predestined!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:13.58,0:05:15.00,Sign,,0,0,0,,{\fade(300,0)\c&H232025&\3c&HC6B7BD&\blur1} Fighter Corps {Attack Wing Crew }Respite Tent {戦闘機隊塔乘員待機室 - I got this with ocr and some characters are clearly of but I'm too lazy to get to the bottom of this}
Dialogue: 0,0:05:15.00,0:05:19.01,Default,,0,0,0,,Say, war correspondent, wanna see Midway personally \Nfrom aboard my Zero?{/..., what do you say if I take you to midway on my zero? - no clue what's the first word, but houdou is "report (of news); reporting; news; information; (media) coverage"}
Dialogue: 0,0:05:19.01,0:05:21.32,Default,,0,0,0,,But I know Zero only has one seat!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:21.32,0:05:24.53,Default,,0,0,0,,Never mind it.{/it's fine, fine} \NWe can seat you behind me, on a pillow.{/we'll place/spread out a zabuton/cushion behind the seat where you can sit}
Dialogue: 0,0:05:24.53,0:05:26.60,Default,,0,0,0,,Should I really do that?{/is it okay}
Dialogue: 0,0:05:26.60,0:05:30.13,Default,,0,0,0,,Naturally! It's faster than a Grumman \Nand has a 20mm cannon.{no clue what's the first word}
Dialogue: 0,0:05:30.13,0:05:32.16,Default,,0,0,0,,You'll get to see an encore of Pearl Harbor.{honestly unsure what he means: I wanted to show you the skill/aptness of pearl harbor}
Dialogue: 0,0:05:32.16,0:05:34.39,Default,,0,0,0,,I can't wait for the enemy's carrier to show up!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:34.39,0:05:37.62,Default,,0,0,0,,No, no, they can stay put, \Nwe'll Pearl Harbor them again!{/if they don't come out, we'll hit ... }
Dialogue: 0,0:05:38.15,0:05:39.40,Default,,0,0,0,,Hey, you alright?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:39.81,0:05:41.63,Default,,0,0,0,,Just a small fever. \NMust be a cold.{/have a bit of a temperature, i wonder if its cold} {Minoru Genda, staff officer of Air Force, also had a fever due to a cold}
Dialogue: 0,0:05:41.63,0:05:43.50,Default,,0,0,0,,Make sure you don't get pneumonia.{/if you catch/end up falling with ..., it's serious}
Dialogue: 0,0:05:43.50,0:05:47.54,Default,,0,0,0,,If a senior gets confined to sick bay, \Nthe lower ranks may also call in sick.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:48.80,0:05:52.32,Default,,0,0,0,,This mist is ideal for clouding enemy's eyes. {/good for for deceiving/fooling enemy's eyes} \NThink they'll come out?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:56.79,0:05:58.19,Default,,0,0,0,,Not until we make them to. {I hope this is what he means by "don't come out first"}
Dialogue: 0,0:05:58.90,0:06:00.56,Default,,0,0,0,,This time, the enemy is careful.{/not carefree}
Dialogue: 0,0:06:00.56,0:06:04.68,Default,,0,0,0,,Even though Yamato and the main forces \Nare well behind, we proceed.{/in addition, ... are coming later/not present} This is unnerving... {/not amusing at all}
Dialogue: 0,0:06:05.54,0:06:07.66,Default,,0,0,0,,If the foe attacks, \Nwe're a sitting duck. {lit: if attacking the enemy, we have to fight naked; hadaka may also mean "concealing nothing; openness" but that still doesn't make sense - this is a deceiving operation in the first place, and what concealing nothing has to do with the absence of yamato?; maybe he means "being uncovered" as "without cover/support" so general message is "we're at disadvantage" as follows from his conversation from another officer}
Dialogue: 0,0:06:07.66,0:06:10.12,Default,,0,0,0,,Battleships are a drag \Nmore than anything. {impediment; burden; encumbrance; hindrance; drag - I think he means they are slow and bulky}
Dialogue: 0,0:06:10.12,0:06:15.25,Default,,0,0,0,,Our pilots are battle-hardened veterans \Nof Pearl Harbor. We can achieve another surprise attack. {rekisen is long military service; having experienced many battles}{/we'll do surprise attack this time as well}
Dialogue: 0,0:06:19.25,0:06:21.95,Default,,0,0,0,,Meanwhile, on the flagship Yamato. {/on the other hand}
Dialogue: 0,0:06:24.36,0:06:27.22,Default,,0,0,0,,Admiral, we have analyzed the enemy's communications. {I hope this is what he means by "examined/checked the calls/summons"} {from wiki: On the afternoon of June 3, the Combined Fleet Headquarters Enemy Squad, boarding the flagship Yamato following the Nagumo task force, intercepted a call code that appeared to be an enemy aircraft carrier near Midway Island. Yamamoto, who was suffering from abdominal pain from roundworms , told his staff to report to the Nagumo Task Force immediately . [121] However, it was postponed due to the judgment that "if the radio blockade is broken, the enemy will know the position" and "the Nagumo Mobile Unit should have intercepted it as well}
Dialogue: 0,0:06:27.22,0:06:31.32,Default,,0,0,0,,Our findings indicate, the enemy's fleet \Nis likely to have left Pearl Harbor. {/conjecture of the current situation; the way it seems is, enemy task force sortied/attacked pearl harbor - again, they clearly use this shutsugeki as "dispatched from"}
Dialogue: 0,0:06:34.66,0:06:36.78,Default,,0,0,0,,Akagi must have caught it too. {I would have liked "catch" in it's infinitive form but alas}
Dialogue: 0,0:06:37.31,0:06:40.88,Default,,0,0,0,,And yet, wouldn't it be safer \Nto inform them personally?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:40.88,0:06:44.05,Default,,0,0,0,,Remember, by doing so, \Nwe reveal Akagi's position to everyone.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:44.05,0:06:46.04,Default,,0,0,0,,However, at the same time on Akagi...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:46.04,0:06:49.82,Default,,0,0,0,,Due to fog, the searchlights{探照灯} are useless, \Nwe have no way of reporting back. {/cannot send a reply signal - reply to what? fuck if i know} {wiki: At 10:30 a.m. on June 3, Japan time, the Nagumo task force was confused in a thick fog, and the flagship Akagi lost sight of Hiryu, Soryu, and two battleships ( Haruna and Kirishima ) . Hiryu and Kirishima were about to collide, so there was some debate about whether to use radio waves at headquarters, but long wave radio waves were used to set the course of the fleet }
Dialogue: 0,0:06:50.92,0:06:52.27,Default,,0,0,0,,Let's use the radio.{/wireless}
Dialogue: 0,0:06:52.27,0:06:55.34,Default,,0,0,0,,We can't. It'd give away our location \Nto the enemy.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:55.34,0:06:59.56,Default,,0,0,0,,Still, as we launch a surprise attack on Midway, \Nthey'll notify their fleet anyway.{/all ships}
Dialogue: 0,0:06:59.56,0:07:02.21,Default,,0,0,0,,And yet, information on the foe{ fleet}'s \Nposition is crucial. {/the problem now is where the enemy fleet}
Dialogue: 0,0:07:02.21,0:07:05.46,Default,,0,0,0,,For the moment, there are no signs \Nof them being dispatched.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:05.46,0:07:09.09,Default,,0,0,0,,If anchored at Pearl Harbor, \Nthey wouldn't make it in time to thwart us. {te wa utsu is "Take necessary measures for the expected situation" so I think it's "even if they hurry, we'll have time to prepare to meet them"}
Dialogue: 0,0:07:10.68,0:07:14.90,Default,,0,0,0,,The probability of an enemy aircraft carrier \Noperating near us is negligible. {/it is unthinkable situation/circumstances that ... is acting ... - either they mean there can't be any carriers nearby now, or that the enemy carrier won't be able to get through our scouts/air defences}
Dialogue: 0,0:07:14.90,0:07:18.46,Default,,0,0,0,,Operational plan involves \Nthat we report on a low frequency wave. {dunno what he means, lit: in order to take action according to plan, since it's unavoidable, hit it on weak radio/phone/signal - maybe they mean reporting back that they proceed to attack with short radio waves/low frequency or someething? or maybe with a short-range radio}
Dialogue: 0,0:07:23.81,0:07:28.88,Default,,0,0,0,,The signal sent from Akagi \Nhas not been caught by the American Pacific Fleet.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:29.78,0:07:35.18,Default,,0,0,0,,However, the general outline of the Midway Operation \Nhas already been known by the American side.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:36.03,0:07:39.87,Default,,0,0,0,,Successful intelligence and code-breaking efforts \Nmade that possible. {/it was thanks to intel. operations and deciphering that have been successful}
Dialogue: 0,0:07:39.87,0:07:42.71,Default,,0,0,0,,Any new information \Non the enemy's task force?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:42.71,0:07:45.21,Default,,0,0,0,,Their whereabouts are still unknown.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:45.21,0:07:49.69,Default,,0,0,0,,On carrier to carrier battle, \Nthe advantage of dealing the blow first is decisive. {/whoever strikes first, wins}
Dialogue: 0,0:07:49.69,0:07:52.83,Default,,0,0,0,,We will keep patrolling the north-northwest area. {/put an emphasis on scouting from north to northwest [of the island]}
Dialogue: 0,0:07:53.95,0:07:56.87,Default,,0,0,0,,Right under their nose, \Nwe'll strike them from the northeast,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:57.38,0:07:58.81,Default,,0,0,0,,As a courtesy for Pearl Harbor. {payback; tit for tat; retaliation; revenge}
Dialogue: 0,0:07:58.81,0:08:06.26,Default,,0,0,0,,American task force hinged up on three carriers - \NEnterprise, Hornet, and Yorktown. {americans were calling carriers flattops at the time btw}
Dialogue: 0,0:08:06.26,0:08:10.32,Default,,0,0,0,,That formation was comparable in size \Nto the task force deployed by Japan. {/matched IJN's task force}
Dialogue: 0,0:08:11.21,0:08:17.20,Default,,0,0,0,,The Japanese and American task forces \Nwere separated only by a measly distance of 240km. {/face each other over a straight line of ...}
Dialogue: 0,0:08:17.20,0:08:20.90,Default,,0,0,0,,As both were plotting an ambush, \Nthe opposing forces were in a deadlock. {/both aiming at a surprise attack, truly as likely as not; 50-50; even match; tie​} {FYI: japanese plan was to start a feint an invasions of Aleutians, then invade midway for real and when they send carriers from PH to relieve midway, intercept them on the way with the main forces; americans read their communications so they prepared an ambush of their own - deployed 3 flattops to the northeast to catch the IJN carriers at a between-sorties period of maximum vulnerability}
Dialogue: 0,0:08:21.45,0:08:26.60,Default,,0,0,0,,The operation was hanging by a thin thread, \Nseparating the victor from the loser by minute proceedings. {this is very perplexing sentence to me and I'm genuinely unsure of it, lit: "competing/contending for difference/variation of instant/moment, big operation's curtain/act is now to be cut/dropped/removed/occur"}
Dialogue: 0,0:08:27.32,0:08:31.95,Default,,0,0,0,,The Midway landing party came under attack. \NSo much for a surprise attack. {/invasion forces were attacked, we can't hope for a ... - he refers to the land troops that were meant to occupy midway in this operation}
Dialogue: 0,0:08:31.95,0:08:34.34,Default,,0,0,0,,The enemy maybe intercepted their communications.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:36.34,0:08:37.73,Default,,0,0,0,,Hey, you should be resting! {/it's okay for you to sleep - it's the same officer who was sick before}
Dialogue: 0,0:08:37.73,0:08:41.13,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm restless anyway, too excited. \NI may as well see our boys off. {lit: it's not for sleeping, my feelings are burning, might as well do sightseeing; watching; viewing - FYI, this is a major }
Dialogue: 0,0:08:41.13,0:08:43.10,Default,,0,0,0,,Wing commander, don't exert yourself! {really unsure how to handle this rank}
Dialogue: 0,0:08:42.58,0:08:44.15,Default,,0,0,0,,{\3c&H042200&}Say, is the patrol plane out?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:44.15,0:08:46.35,Default,,0,0,0,,No, it'll take off with 1st wave squadron.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:46.35,0:08:47.45,Default,,0,0,0,,All-at-once strategy? {lit: one-step strategy? - I think he refers to the japanese doctrine of the time which had it that all the aircraft take off and operate as one big blob, at the same time, with one decisive hit, as opposed to american doctrine of piecemeal attacks}
Dialogue: 0,0:08:47.45,0:08:48.65,Default,,0,0,0,,Business as usual. {just like always}
Dialogue: 0,0:08:48.65,0:08:53.08,Default,,0,0,0,,What if the patrol aircraft spots an enemy fleet \Nas the strike on Midway is underway?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:53.08,0:08:55.95,Default,,0,0,0,,Let them, the 2nd wave {of attack }\Nis armed with torpedoes and all set. {/is on standby}
Dialogue: 0,0:09:00.64,0:09:02.45,Default,,0,0,0,,1st wave wing takeoff!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:51.49,0:09:54.12,Default,,0,0,0,,Show 'em hell! That's it! {guess}
Dialogue: 0,0:10:07.24,0:10:09.62,Default,,0,0,0,,What's with the patrol aircraft?{/happened to} \NIs it in order? {koshou is "fault; trouble; breakdown; failure; being out of order"}
Dialogue: 0,0:10:10.09,0:10:12.09,Default,,0,0,0,,It's running 30 minutes late already. {I really dunno what this refers to - whether they mean it failed to launch or failed to report or w/e; wiki only has this to say: "For this reason, the Chikuma machine (04:35) 1:35 am (5th search line), (04:38) 1:38 am (6th search line), the Type 0 water reconnaissance plane will start, ( 04 : 50) Anti-submarine patrol aircraft launched at 1:50 a.m. [161] [162] . Tone (04:38) anti-submarine patrol aircraft at 1:38 a.m., (04:42) 1:42 a.m. (3rd search line), (05:00) 2:00 a.m. (4th search line) [161] [163] each launched a water reconnaissance . The detailed battle report states that ``Tone and Chikuma will be significantly delayed,''" - so apparently, they are delayed in starting}
Dialogue: 0,0:10:19.66,0:10:21.83,Default,,0,0,0,,Hey-hey, why are they still fiddling with it?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:21.83,0:10:23.17,Default,,0,0,0,,What could be the matter?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:55.41,0:10:57.81,Default,,0,0,0,,Show up, Grumman. \NAssume attacking formation! {trusting HA here, no clue what is first or last word}
Dialogue: 0,0:11:55.81,0:11:57.86,Default,,0,0,0,,Enemy plane on starboard!{hope its migi teki} 166 degrees!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:01.48,0:12:03.87,Default,,0,0,0,,It is close enough in distance to tell - it's the enemy. {very tenuous line and HA's " It's an enemy plane " is clearly incomplete}
Dialogue: 0,0:12:03.87,0:12:05.66,Default,,0,0,0,,No, it's a flying boat. {I think this moment is so intense because the reconnaissance flying boats are launched from ships, meaning the american fleet is nearby; wiki: "At around 2:15 am (05:15), a PBY Catalina flying boat piloted by Captain Addy spotted a Japanese reconnaissance seaplane (Tone No. 4) [170] , and the captain determined that a Japanese fleet was nearby. As a result of searching the area, he found the Nagumo unit 15 minutes later and reported in plain text, "Japanese aircraft carrier 1, Midway at 320 degrees, 150 degrees " . The Japanese side also found a PBY flying boat, and a smoke screen was raised from the light cruiser Nagara of the patrol squadron , followed by the battleship Kirishima, announcing the discovery of the enemy aircraft . The Nagumo Task Force began launching the Zero Squadron to directly cover (support), but the American flying boat continued contact while using clouds to avoid it, and the Zero Squadron was finally unable to shoot down Captain Addy's PBY flying boat. "}
Dialogue: 0,0:12:12.80,0:12:14.99,Default,,0,0,0,,Prepare for anti-aircraft combat!{HA's "Anti-aircraft combat with all staff!" is clearly incomplete but I'd trust the general direction of his thought here}
Dialogue: 0,0:12:14.99,0:12:16.42,Default,,0,0,0,,Personnel in position!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:32.62,0:12:34.42,Default,,0,0,0,,Cowards, hiding behind the clouds!{/damn it's trying to run away}
Dialogue: 0,0:12:37.50,0:12:43.12,Default,,0,0,0,,The Japanese Mobile Fleet could not have anticipated \Nthe sudden deployment of American Aircraft Carriers. {/wasn't expecting ... to draw near them}
Dialogue: 0,0:12:44.09,0:12:47.41,Default,,0,0,0,,And yet, there they were drawing near, {/coming}
Dialogue: 0,0:12:48.35,0:12:49.46,Default,,0,0,0,,Steadily. {shikamo is just "moreover; furthermore" but here it's not followed by anything so Idk what it means}
Dialogue: 0,0:12:56.98,0:13:03.17,Default,,0,0,0,,Enemy task force spotted. Four aircraft carriers, \Nseveral battleships, distance 280km, course - 150 degrees. {I'm not sure if the course here is like the relative direction if you look from yorktown or like the absolute celestial course they're on}
Dialogue: 0,0:13:07.93,0:13:10.26,Default,,0,0,0,,No response from the patrol aircraft yet?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:10.26,0:13:12.91,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes. We've not heard from them as of yet.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:45.76,0:13:46.72,Default,,0,0,0,,Shit...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:46.72,0:13:50.67,Default,,0,0,0,,Hey, call the headquarters on Akagi, \Na 2nd wave wing is needed. {/contact Commander-in-Chief/admiral}
Dialogue: 0,0:13:50.67,0:13:52.14,Default,,0,0,0,,The radio station is busted. {trust HA's "The telegraph is out of order" here}
Dialogue: 0,0:13:52.14,0:13:54.36,Default,,0,0,0,,Cretin! Fix it, then. It's your job!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:54.36,0:13:55.44,Default,,0,0,0,,Roger!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:58.50,0:13:59.49,Default,,0,0,0,,This is nasty...{/this guy}
Dialogue: 0,0:14:00.17,0:14:02.28,Default,,0,0,0,,Ouch! Hot!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:02.28,0:14:04.27,Default,,0,0,0,,Can't be helped. \NAsk another plane to do it.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:04.27,0:14:04.74,Default,,0,0,0,,Roger!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:11.89,0:14:14.32,Default,,0,0,0,,We've received a signal \Nfrom the 1st wave wing.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:14.32,0:14:18.31,Default,,0,0,0,,"1st wave of attack ended, returning home. \N2nd wave is required." {/we've finished the attack, arriving to base, need a second wave}
Dialogue: 0,0:14:18.31,0:14:22.95,Default,,0,0,0,,The enemy's combined air power numbers 400 planes. \NTheir pilots are also superior.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:22.95,0:14:25.23,Default,,0,0,0,,The moment we can emerge victorious is...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:25.23,0:14:28.73,Default,,0,0,0,,When their attack on Midway stops \Nas the planes retreat to the carrier... {/after attacking midway, as the enemy returns on the flattop}
Dialogue: 0,0:14:28.73,0:14:29.81,Default,,0,0,0,,Precisely.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:29.81,0:14:33.22,Default,,0,0,0,,The enemy is about 380km away from Midway.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:33.22,0:14:35.10,Default,,0,0,0,,According to the Intel received at 6:40,{genzai is "now/at the moment" so im not sure what moment he is talking about}
Dialogue: 0,0:14:35.10,0:14:37.04,Default,,0,0,0,,The foe is advancing towards the attack wing, {lit: in order to accomodate/house/seat the attack wing - they use this shuuyou as "to receive/let land after sortie"}
Dialogue: 0,0:14:37.04,0:14:38.92,Default,,0,0,0,,at the speed of 25 knots.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:40.13,0:14:44.27,Default,,0,0,0,,If we were to sortie now, \Nour planes would only have to travel 270km, {/allied attack would fly only ...}
Dialogue: 0,0:14:44.27,0:14:46.88,Default,,0,0,0,,Arriving at the enemy location \Nduring the refueling. {this shyuuyou again - lit: when the enemy's carrier is receiving the attack wing after sortie...}
Dialogue: 0,0:14:46.88,0:14:49.32,Default,,0,0,0,,Thus, seizing a golden chance for offensive. {/in other words, a ... presents itself}
Dialogue: 0,0:14:53.00,0:14:57.81,Default,,0,0,0,,This would be especially efficient \Nif we get the planes stationed on Midway to also attack. {lit: if we let land-borne planes from midway attack first, revenge would be successful - I'm not if it's still the payback for PH or just general "counterattack"}
Dialogue: 0,0:14:58.85,0:15:02.85,Default,,0,0,0,,To game successfully, \Ntiming is the key, before we overwhelm them!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:02.85,0:15:05.84,Default,,0,0,0,,{The moment of }A Surprise attack. \NOur golden chance!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:06.38,0:15:08.09,Default,,0,0,0,,Give it all you've got, Admiral. {using all of one's strength (to); giving (it) everything one has got; going full-out​; kakka is just "someone superior"}
Dialogue: 0,0:15:28.34,0:15:34.54,Default,,0,0,0,,Meanwhile, on the Japanese side, no sighting \Nof the American carrier had been recorded as of yet. {/no reports were received of spotting ...}
Dialogue: 0,0:15:45.94,0:15:47.29,Default,,0,0,0,,Any news from the patrol plane? {/no reports/signals/contacts ...}
Dialogue: 0,0:15:47.29,0:15:48.30,Default,,0,0,0,,Negative.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:59.54,0:16:01.85,Default,,0,0,0,,The area is swarming with enemy flying boats. {trusting HA's "There are many enemy flying boats" here as idk wht's chidatsuku, i don't suppose it's to flicker; to glimmer; to flit}
Dialogue: 0,0:16:02.32,0:16:05.52,Default,,0,0,0,,Theoretically, \Nthe enemy is using 1/3 of his planes for scouting. {/I've heard enemy is using 1/3 of his total strength ...}
Dialogue: 0,0:16:05.52,0:16:07.17,Default,,0,0,0,, Even so, they are too numerous.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:07.17,0:16:09.52,Default,,0,0,0,,Even if their fleet \Nhad a hunch of what's going on, {/realized}
Dialogue: 0,0:16:09.52,0:16:11.88,Default,,0,0,0,,They would only be \Nfreshly off from Pearl Harbor.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:11.88,0:16:13.47,Default,,0,0,0,,Do we launch the 2nd wave? {/do we start second wave of attack?}
Dialogue: 0,0:16:17.47,0:16:19.54,Default,,0,0,0,,Prepare the 2nd wave of attack on Midway!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:19.54,0:16:20.49,Default,,0,0,0,,Roger!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:21.14,0:16:23.55,Default,,0,0,0,,Replace the torpedo mounting with ground bombs! {/hurry up and replace torpedo ordnance on the planes still onboard with land-purposed bombs}{fyi, right now, they were expecting some american fleet to show up and thus armed the remaining planes with torpedoes, while the first wave is still on its way back}
Dialogue: 0,0:16:23.55,0:16:24.17,Default,,0,0,0,,Roger!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:25.53,0:16:27.04,Default,,0,0,0,,Get the emergency conversion going! {/hurry up to convert lightning-fast}
Dialogue: 0,0:17:11.32,0:17:12.43,Default,,0,0,0,,Faster!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:13.61,0:17:15.61,Default,,0,0,0,,Enemy approaching! \NFour aircraft! {HA has it " 4 enemies, over the horizon" and I'd trust, too lazy} {btw, those are b-17 from midway}
Dialogue: 0,0:17:40.66,0:17:42.56,Default,,0,0,0,,Six more enemy bombers this way!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:25.58,0:18:27.25,Default,,0,0,0,,Eat this!{/did it}
Dialogue: 0,0:18:31.05,0:18:32.27,Default,,0,0,0,,Take off, faster!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:34.76,0:18:37.60,Default,,0,0,0,,Enemy patrol aircraft. \NWe've been discovered.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:41.37,0:18:46.78,Default,,0,0,0,,Tone's vehicle 4 reports: locating 10 "enemy-like" ships, \Nabout 10 degrees away from Midway.{https://ja.wikipedia.org/wiki/%E5%88%A9%E6%A0%B9_(%E9%87%8D%E5%B7%A1%E6%B4%8B%E8%89%A6) ; /unit 4 (I assume, scouting plane); I assume they mean "10 degrees of azimuth if you accept midway as zero"}
Dialogue: 0,0:18:48.00,0:18:50.15,Default,,0,0,0,,What do they mean by "enemy-like”?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:51.83,0:18:52.74,Default,,0,0,0,,A carrier?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:53.29,0:18:54.10,Default,,0,0,0,,A carrier!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:55.74,0:18:58.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Bridge to Tone,{no clue what is kie part and HA just ignored it} \Nreckon the enemy fleet composition.{/we need to know about the types of ships in the enemy fleet}
Dialogue: 0,0:19:08.38,0:19:15.16,Default,,0,0,0,,Tone's vehicle 4 reports: enemy forces are 5 cruisers, \Nand 5 destroyers. The carrier is seemingly not present.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:29.27,0:19:33.29,Default,,0,0,0,,The enemy is accompanied \Nby a "carrier-like" vessel in the rear. {/after ..., what follows after them is a ship that resembles a carrier}
Dialogue: 0,0:19:35.29,0:19:36.45,Default,,0,0,0,,They're here? {/came}
Dialogue: 0,0:19:44.47,0:19:47.04,Default,,0,0,0,,It only states "carrier-like." \NWe need hard confirm. {/it's not certain yet, isn't it}
Dialogue: 0,0:19:47.04,0:19:49.23,Default,,0,0,0,,With "-like" upon "-like." \NNothing is certain. {/it was "lookalike" before as well; no clue what's after kuchi, would assume it's something about talking carelessly/talking without any proof}
Dialogue: 0,0:19:53.26,0:19:56.86,Default,,0,0,0,,A request from Hiryu's second squadron commander:
Dialogue: 0,0:19:56.86,0:19:59.86,Default,,0,0,0,,It is crucial that the attack wings \Ntake off at once. {unsure of the whole message, the last part lit is "cornerstone; main point; keystone/need/pivot - recognize/notice/deem/approve it"}
Dialogue: 0,0:20:06.18,0:20:07.37,Default,,0,0,0,,Admiral.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:07.37,0:20:09.75,Default,,0,0,0,,The 1st wave vehicles are on their way back. {/first attack is returning}
Dialogue: 0,0:20:09.75,0:20:12.90,Default,,0,0,0,,Dispatching the attack wings \Nwithout any fighter coverage is risky. {lit: hit/damaged aircraft are present, too, if only the attack flies - I think he means the attacking planes are too vulnerable if sent out without fighters' cover, but why would he put those two clauses in that order then? maybe he means "among returning planes some need repairs, if this way we'll send only the attack group" - like as in "we'll be left without air cover ourselves"?}
Dialogue: 0,0:20:13.40,0:20:14.18,Default,,0,0,0,,Look!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:14.75,0:20:19.63,Default,,0,0,0,,Then, fighters, bombers, torpedo bombers \Nwill deal a decisive blow as one. {ha: let's attack with the trinity of ...; lit: 3 names in one body - we'll have senkouhou - not sure what is the last word, but may have to do with "scoring first" and "cannon"; I think he means we'll wait until all 3 are fully loaded and ready and then they take off all at once" - again, in accordance with japanese doctrine}
Dialogue: 0,0:20:20.51,0:20:23.99,Default,,0,0,0,,As soon as the 1st wave lands,{this shuuyou again, /received/at home} \Nthe entire fleet heads north-east.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:23.99,0:20:26.58,Default,,0,0,0,,We'll rearm for the all-in attack {/with all forces}\Nand crush the enemy.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:26.58,0:20:28.60,Default,,0,0,0,,Prepare for anti-ship warfare! {lit: attack changes to sailing ship; sailing boat; sailing vessel}
Dialogue: 0,0:20:28.60,0:20:30.39,Default,,0,0,0,,Arm all the planes with torpedoes!{majorly a guess}
Dialogue: 0,0:20:28.95,0:20:29.85,Default,,0,0,0,,The Hell?!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:29.85,0:20:31.07,Default,,0,0,0,,Gotta switch them again! {lit: swap/exchange/replacement/switch again}
Dialogue: 0,0:20:31.07,0:20:31.93,Default,,0,0,0,,Hurry up!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:31.93,0:20:33.92,Default,,0,0,0,,Commence the emergency conversion! {same as before}
Dialogue: 0,0:20:55.54,0:20:56.94,Default,,0,0,0,,On the carrier Hiryu...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:57.49,0:21:03.05,Default,,0,0,0,,Transmission from Akagi. Once the 1st wave lands, \Ncommence the emergency conversion and head north-east.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:03.78,0:21:04.13,Default,,0,0,0,, What?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:05.12,0:21:09.61,Default,,0,0,0,,As soon as Tone's patrol aircraft was spotted, \Nthe enemy dispatched their attack wings...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:09.61,0:21:14.11,Default,,0,0,0,,Which means, two hours later, around 10:20 \Nwe will come under attack! {maybe he means 2 hours after they had dispatched attack wings, not "from now"}
Dialogue: 0,0:21:14.63,0:21:17.02,Default,,0,0,0,,They think we can afford \Nto wait for the 1st wave?!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:17.52,0:21:19.50,Default,,0,0,0,,We have no time to mount torpedoes!{/we don't have time to change/convert into}
Dialogue: 0,0:21:19.50,0:21:21.68,Default,,0,0,0,,They must take off \Nwith whatever setup they have! {/just fly with land bomb attached/carrying}
Dialogue: 0,0:21:21.68,0:21:24.04,Default,,0,0,0,,Anything's fine against their carrier! Fools! {/it's alright if they hit enemy carrier - either he means they can use land bomb on carrier just fine or "if they can just attack the carrier with whatever, that would be enough"}
Dialogue: 0,0:21:24.65,0:21:27.82,Default,,0,0,0,,The reckoning of Hiryu's captain \Nhit the nail's head. {/this hiryu commander calculations come true}
Dialogue: 0,0:21:27.82,0:21:33.12,Default,,0,0,0,,The formation of American bombers that took off \Nfrom Enterprise, alongside its task force escort
Dialogue: 0,0:21:33.12,0:21:34.71,Default,,0,0,0,,was already on the way. {/exactly according to plan/calculations}
Dialogue: 0,0:21:34.71,0:21:37.04,Default,,0,0,0,,They seized their golden chance.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:37.60,0:21:43.61,Default,,0,0,0,,The 1st wave vehicles finally landed \Nwhile the 2nd wave was just merely preparing to take off... {lit: at that exact moment now, when the housing of the first wave is finished and the second wave is about to depart}
Dialogue: 0,0:21:59.13,0:22:00.98,Default,,0,0,0,,Admiral! Kaga is attacked!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:00.98,0:22:02.15,Default,,0,0,0,,Emergency takeoff! {ha: Take off as soon as you are ready, lit: hurry up to launch}
Dialogue: 0,0:22:02.69,0:22:05.10,Default,,0,0,0,,Every battle-ready vehicle takes off immediately! {lit: attack preparations finished aircraft take off}
Dialogue: 0,0:22:10.68,0:22:12.19,Default,,0,0,0,,Swoop! {sudden drop; sharp fall; nosedive; swoop}
Dialogue: 0,0:22:22.29,0:22:23.36,Default,,0,0,0,,Watch out!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:05.91,0:23:07.86,Default,,0,0,0,,Damn it, just five more minutes...
Dialogue: 0,0:23:07.86,0:23:11.30,Default,,0,0,0,,If only the enemy was five minutes late, \Nwe'd be in a lot better place! {/we wouldn't have been beaten so badly}
Dialogue: 0,0:23:11.30,0:23:14.29,Default,,0,0,0,,Wrong, it's not five minutes, \Nbut two hours.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:14.81,0:23:17.33,Default,,0,0,0,,We missed our last big shot{ for victory} two hours ago.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:17.96,0:23:19.38,Default,,0,0,0,,Alright, I'll strike back!{lit: Alright, this time I'll do it - I've no clue what this is about, but because hiryu was the last undamaged carrier and he is her captain, I'd assume he means "we'll dispatch our own bombers and follow the enemy to his carrier" like it happened irl}
Dialogue: 0,0:23:26.28,0:23:27.82,Default,,0,0,0,,In just five minutes,
Dialogue: 0,0:23:28.53,0:23:31.26,Default,,0,0,0,,the Battle for Midway turned into a debacle. {lit: left a grudge}
Dialogue: 0,0:23:31.26,0:23:35.10,Default,,0,0,0,,However, some say, \Nthis outcome with such time window was obvious
Dialogue: 0,0:23:35.89,0:23:41.75,Default,,0,0,0,,The ability to think several moves ahead and \Napply aptly calculations after decision taking
Dialogue: 0,0:23:41.75,0:23:43.78,Default,,0,0,0,,is what sets apart a victor from a loser. {/only he who can do meticulous calculation and use the product of those calculations in times of decision can become a true winner}
Dialogue: 0,0:23:45.00,0:23:49.86,Default,,0,0,0,,Those indulging on wishful thinking, \Nlosing sight of their objectives at a given time,
Dialogue: 0,0:23:49.86,0:23:52.45,Default,,0,0,0,,are liable to experience disaster. {/the tragedy certainly comes to them}
Dialogue: 0,0:23:56.87,0:24:06.63,Sign,,0,0,0,,{\fade(100,0)}The most crucial moment in life is during decision making.\NThe Pacific War taught us the preciousness of peace.\NBut also instilled numerous lessons on how to live.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:08.99,0:24:11.32,Default,,0,0,0,,Akagi, Kaga, Soryu -
Dialogue: 0,0:24:11.32,0:24:15.35,Default,,0,0,0,,in an instant, three carriers \Nwere lost in the battle of Midway
Dialogue: 0,0:24:15.35,0:24:17.83,Default,,0,0,0,,The only carrier still afloat being Hiryu.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:17.83,0:24:22.60,Default,,0,0,0,,Faced with American advantage of three carriers to one, \NHiryu commits to a suicidal raid. {lit is "putting one's life on the line; giving everything one has got; acting out of desperation raid; attack; assault"} {remember what I told you about how she sent 3 bombers after the returning american ones}
Dialogue: 0,0:24:23.62,0:24:25.58,Default,,0,0,0,,In a three-on-one battle,
Dialogue: 0,0:24:26.29,0:24:30.21,Default,,0,0,0,,next week comes the tragic fate \Nof the aircraft carrier Hiryu. {tragic but brave; heroic; grim; pathetic}
Dialogue: 0,0:24:30.21,0:24:35.24,Default,,0,0,0,,With the decision of her captain, \Nthe Battle for Midway meets its end.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:30.66,0:24:37.51,Sign,,0,0,0,,{\fade(0,300)}{ミッドウェイ海戦(後編)}Animentary: Decision\NEpisode 3 \NBattle of Midway (Part 2){\N Please look forward to it next week}
